cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with cross language plagiarism detection using translation tools. It also involves the use of natural language processing techniques such as stop word removal and stemming. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the use of Google Search API for information retrieval. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it uses fingerprint matching technique, which is a widely used plagiarism detection technique and involves the use of Google Translate API for translation. 

Finally, it could also be categorized under cs.DL (Deep Learning) as deep learning techniques are often used in natural language processing tasks such as translation and plagiarism detection.
